\">14</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+10</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+9</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">56</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">7</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">18th</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">15</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+11</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+9</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">60</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">8</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">19th</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">15</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+11</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+9</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">60</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">8</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">20th</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">16</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+12</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+10</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">64</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">8</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">3</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Class Level:&nbsp;The character&rsquo;s necromancer level. The necromancer&rsquo;s class levels stack with levels of any other classes that are entitled to a bone commander for the purpose of determining the bone commander&rsquo;s statistics.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>HD:&nbsp;This is the total number of eight-<wbr />sided (d8) Hit Dice the bone commander possesses, but it possesses no Constitution score. Bone commanders use their Charisma score in place of their Constitution score.</p>\n<p>BAB:&nbsp;This is the bone commander&rsquo;s base attack bonus. Bone commanders do not gain additional attacks using their natural weapons for a high base attack bonus.</p>\n<p>Fort/Ref/Will:&nbsp;These are the bone commander&rsquo;s base saving throw bonuses. A bone commander has good Will saves.</p>\n<p>Skills:&nbsp;This lists the total skill ranks for the bone commander. Bone commanders can assign skill ranks to any skill listed below. A bone commander cannot have more ranks in a skill than it has Hit Dice.</p>\n<p>Bone commanders can have ranks in any of the following skills:</p>\n<p>Acrobatics, Climb, Disguise, Intimidate, Knowledge (arcana), Knowledge (religion), Perception, Sense Motive, Spellcraft, Stealth, and Swim. In addition, at 1st level, the necromancer can choose 4 additional skills to be class skills for his bone commander.</p>\n<p>Feats:&nbsp;This is the total number of feats possessed by a bone commander. Bone commanders can select any feat that they qualify for. Bone commander feats are set once chosen.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/classes/core-classes/archer/#aim\"><span lang=\"en-US\">Aim</span></a>&nbsp;as an&nbsp;<span lang=\"en-US\">archer</span>&nbsp;of the same level as its hit dice &ndash; 3 (minimum of 1) and gains weapon and armor proficiencies of an archer.</p>","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[{"_id":"lcnjxowa","formula":"floor(@classes.boneCommanderHd.level/3)","operator":"add","target":"","subTarget":"nac","modifier":"base","priority":0,"value":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"links":{"children":[],"classAssociations":[{"name":"Aim","level":1,"uuid":"Compendium.ffd20-content.ffd20-class-pack-core_archer.6F17p6x2hj7pMg3B"}]},"tag":"boneCommanderHd","useCustomTag":true,"armorProf":{"value":["lgt"],"custom":""},"weaponProf":{"value":["sim"],"custom":"all non-exotic bows;all non-exotic 