">5th</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">20th</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">16</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+12</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">+10</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">64</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">8</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">51</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">6th</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Class Level:&nbsp;The character&rsquo;s necromancer level. The necromancer&rsquo;s class levels stack with levels of any other classes that are entitled to a bone commander for the purpose of determining the bone commander&rsquo;s statistics.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>HD:&nbsp;This is the total number of eight-<wbr />sided (d8) Hit Dice the bone commander possesses, but it possesses no Constitution score. Bone commanders use their Charisma score in place of their Constitution score.</p>\n<p>BAB:&nbsp;This is the bone commander&rsquo;s base attack bonus. Bone commanders do not gain additional attacks using their natural weapons for a high base attack bonus.</p>\n<p>Fort/Ref/Will:&nbsp;These are the bone commander&rsquo;s base saving throw bonuses. A bone commander has good Will saves.</p>\n<p>Skills:&nbsp;This lists the total skill ranks for the bone commander. Bone commanders can assign skill ranks to any skill listed below. A bone commander cannot have more ranks in a skill than it has Hit Dice.</p>\n<p>Bone commanders can have ranks in any of the following skills:</p>\n<p>Acrobatics, Climb, Disguise, Intimidate, Knowledge (arcana), Knowledge (religion), Perception, Sense Motive, Spellcraft, Stealth, and Swim. In addition, at 1st level, the necromancer can choose 4 additional skills to be class skills for his bone commander.</p>\n<p>Feats:&nbsp;This is the total number of feats possessed by a bone commander. Bone commanders can select any feat that they qualify for. Bone commander feats are set once chosen.</p>\n<p>gains a MP pool, cantrips, spells as a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/classes/core-classes/black-mage/\">black mage</a>&nbsp;of the same level as its hit dice with a capped spell level of 6th (See below.), and gains weapon and armor proficiencies of a black mage.</p>","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[{"_id":"lcnjxowa","formula":"floor(@classes.boneCommanderHd.level/3)","operator":"add","target":"","subTarget":"nac","modifier":"base","priority":0,"value":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"links":{"children":[],"classAssociations":[{"name":"Spells/Cantrips - Black Mage","level":1,"uuid":"Compendium.ffd20-content.ffd20-class-pack-core_black-mage.jwbuV6eiLJ6YiWaz"}]},"tag":"boneCommanderHd","useCustomTag":true,"armorProf":{"value":[],"custom":""},"weaponProf":{"value":[],"custom":"dagger;sling;power rod;power staff;animated dolls;quarterstaff"},"languages":{"value":[],"custom":""},"flags":{"boolean":{},"dictionary":{}},"scriptCalls":[],"subType":"base","classSubType":"none","parentClass":"Necromancer","level":2,"lvl":0,"countforexp":"exp","hd":8,"hp":8,"classCastingStat":"int","classBaseMPTypes":"pacman","classBaseMPauto":"yes","mp":0,"bab":"med","skillsPerLevel":4,"savingThrows":{"fort":{"value":"low"},"ref":{"value":"low"},"will":{"value":"high"}},"fc":{"hp":{"value":0},"skill":{"value":0},"alt":{"value":0,"notes":""}},"classSkills":{"acr":true,"apr":false,"blf":false,"clm":true,"crf":false,"dip":false,"dev":false,"dis":true,"dri":false,"esc":false,"fly":false,"han":false,"hea":false,"int":true,"kar":true,"kdu":false,"ken":false,"kge":false,"khi":false,"klo":false,"kna":false,"kno":false,"kpl":false,"kre":true,"kte":false,"lin":false,"nav":false,"per":true,"prf":false,"pil":false,"pro":false,"rep":false,"rid":false,"sen":true,"slt":false,"spl":true,"ste":true,"sur":false,"swm":true,"umd":false},"levels":{"value":0,"_deprecated":true},